# 5. 必要なものは

Akito: ♪————!! ————!!
Ken: Akito, you're still too tense!
Akito: ♪——! ——...!
Akito: ♪...——!
Akito: (How many hours have we been practicing...?)
Akito: (My brain's not getting enough oxygen because of all this singing...)
Ken: Let's stop here for today... You're at your limit.
Akito: ...
Akito: Okay... Got it...
Akito: (No... Again, why...?)
Akito: (Even though Ken's working with me one-on-one, I can't produce any results...still...)
Ken: (I've been trying every trick I know, but those shackles won't come off easily...)
Ken: (I guess that's only natural... After all, this is what brought Akito this far.)
Ken: ... Hey, Akito?
Ken: Why don't we go for a drive?
Akito: Now...?
Ken: Let's make a pit stop here. Want something to drink?
Akito: Uh, sure...
Akito: (Well, I accepted Ken's invitation, and now we're here...)
Akito: (So, he actually just felt like going for a drive...?)
Akito: (Or was he trying to give me a breath of fresh air because I was having trouble focusing?)
Ken: Here, have a cafe au lait. It's hot, so be careful.
Akito: Thank you.
Akito: (How long has it been since the last time I just sat and did nothing like this?)
Akito: (Lately, I've been practicing as soon as I wake up, then going to school, a live house after that and singing with Ken at the end... There's been no time in that schedule for me to relax...)
Akito: (But...)
Akito: (Is it okay for me to be doing this right now?)
Akito: (Wouldn't it be better for me to use this time to practice instead...?)
Ken: ...
Ken: This reminds me of the first time I met you.
Akito: What?
Ken: Do you remember? The first time we spoke to each other on Vivid Street.
Akito: Oh...
Ken: What's wrong, kid?
Junior High School Akito: Huh? You're from RADder... What are you...?
Ken: Here, drink this. Mind if I sit next to you?
Akito: You remember how we met, Ken?
Ken: Yeah, like it happened yesterday. The way you looked like you were about to start sobbing is hard to forget.
Akito: No, you should definitely forget about that...
Ken: You've changed so much since then.
Ken: You came this far by following your heart. I couldn't be more impressed.
Akito: Thank you very much.
Ken: So, tell me. What was it like sprinting at full speed until now?
Akito: What was it like...?
Akito: I dunno...
Akito: So much has happened. I'm not sure how to put it into words...
Ken: Just like that.
Akito: Ow...! Wh-Why'd you flick my forehead...?
Ken: So that you don't forget how you felt just now.
Ken: Akito. Next time, sing with that feeling in mind.
Akito: Wait, you mean...?
Ken: Don't worry. You already have everything you need.
Ken: All you have to do now is realize that and sing.
Akito: ...
Ken: Oh, it's getting late. We should start heading back.
Akito: Oh...
Akito: Okay.
Ken: You're sure you don't want me to take you further than the station?
Akito: Yes, since the trains are still running. Thank you for working with me this late.
Ken: No problem. Just make sure to get some rest. See you later.
Ken: Don't worry. You already have everything you need.
Ken: All you have to do now is realize that and sing.
Akito: I just need to realize it, huh?
Akito: (Based on what Ken said, it feels like the answer should be right in front of me.)
Akito: (I'm one step away from finding that thing I've been missing...)
Kohane: I have all of you to thank...
Kohane: Miku, you guys... Shinonome, Aoyagi, An...
Kohane: I am who I am now because of all of you.
Akito: (Yeah...)
Akito: (I don't have to worry about everything on my own.)
Akito: I should head over there.
Luka: Oh, Akito, hello!
Len: Welcome! Were you guys practicing again today?
Akito: Yeah, we were.
MEIKO: Then, please take a seat. I'm sure you're tired, so let me get you something to drink.
Akito: Oh, thank you...
Luka: MEIKO told me everything! You've all been going around to different live houses to perform at them, right?
Luka: That sounds like so much fun. I'd love to see the live houses in your world.
MEIKO: Luka, remember what I told you the other day? You shouldn't interrupt them needlessly.
Luka: I know.
Luka: Still, what has training at these live houses involved? You must have been singing with some really good performers.
Akito: Yeah, we have...
Akito: They're on a completely different level compared to us. We have to do everything we can just to keep up with them.
Akito: We have a planning meeting during the drive over after school, sing at the live house, do a debrief on our way home, then do it all over again...
Akito: Fortunately, we've somehow been managing to hold our ground... ...
Akito: With that in mind, can I ask you guys something?
Len: Wait, Akito, you've been practicing with An's dad...?!
Akito: Yeah. For a few weeks now.
Akito: But I'm having a lot of trouble making any progress...
Akito: I understand what Ken's telling me to do, but I can't figure out how to put that into practice.
MEIKO: Yes, based on what you just told us, that does seem very tricky...
MEIKO: Relax and sing from your heart. Turn your feelings into song.
MEIKO: That's easier said than done. In terms of actually accomplishing those things...
Luka: Hmmm... That's a tough one. This is all about intuition...
Luka: Wait, I know...!
Luka: Akito. Would you mind singing something for us?
Akito: Huh? Now...?
Luka: Yes! I think hearing you actually sing will make it easier for us to give you proper advice.
MEIKO: She has a point. I think we'd all like to hear you sing.
Akito: Okay, then... If you all don't mind listening...
Akito: (A lot of time's passed since I last sang here because I've been practicing in our world so much...)
Akito: (But this is my chance to hear from Luka and the others about my singing.)
Akito: (This might lead me to the answer...!)
Akito: (Take your feelings...and turn them into song...)
Akito: ♪————!!
Akito: *Sigh* How did I do...?
MEIKO: That was incredible. I think I've got goosebumps...
Len: Yeah...! You sent shivers down my spine! You've gotten so much better, Akito!!
Akito: I mean, I have been practicing basically nonstop.
Akito: But tell me more. What else did you guys notice?
Luka: Hmm...
MEIKO: Luka...?
Luka: You sounded really amazing just now, Akito...
Luka: But I feel like you can do a lot more! Like, pow!
Akito: Pow...?
MEIKO: I know what you're trying to say, but you need to be more specific with your advice...
Luka: Wh-What?! But!
Luka: I mean, Akito, I'm guessing that you're feeling a lot of different things right now...
Luka: You're happy about getting to practice with Ken. You're excited, and you want to make him proud, but you're nervous at the same time...
Luka: You should just let that all out. Pow!
Len: Hmm...
Akito: In other words, I'm not letting my feelings flow freely...
Luka: There's that... But... How do I put it...? Oh.
Luka: Akito!
Luka: Why don't we do what you and Ken have been doing? Let's sing together.
Akito: What...?
